definition.value: An organic cation obtained by protonation at position 3 in the oxazole ring of N-demethylindolmycin. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An organic cation obtained by protonation at position 3 in the oxazole ring of indolmycin. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

A 29 amino acid polypeptide that is used to treat growth problems (usually in children) due to growth hormone deficiency. It is the biologically active fragment of human growth hormone-releasing factor (GHRH).
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (R)-3-(indol-3-yl)-2-oxobutyric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A dicarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphino group of phosphinomethylmalic acid.
A hydrochloride obtained by combining ZM 323881 with one molar equivalent of hydrochloric acid.
A guaiacyl lignin that is guaiacylglycerol in which the hydrogen on the 2-hydroxy function has been replaced by a 4-(1,2,3-trihydroxypropan-1-yl)-2,6-dimethoxyphenyl group.
A guaiacyl lignin obtained by cyclodimerisation of coniferol.
A member of the class of quinazolines carrying 2-fluoro-4-methyl-5-hydroxyanilino and benzyloxy substituents at positions 4 and 7 respectively.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino function of ZM 323881.
A hydrochloride obtained by combining the free base of GS4012 with one molar equivalent of hydrochloric acid.
Any activator of vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF).
An indole alkaloid that is 18-oxayohimban dehydrogenated at positions 3, 4, 5, 6, 16 and 17 and substituted by a methyl group at the 19alpha position and by a methoxycarbonyl group at position 16.
A member of the class of pyridines that is 2-(pyridin-4-yl)ethane-1-thiol in which the thiol hydrogen is replaced by a 4-methoxyphenyl group.
A pyridinium ion obtained by protonation of the pyridine nitrogen of GS4012 free base.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-KI16425.
An antagonist that binds to and deactivates lysophosphatidic acid receptors.

A member of the class of isoxazoles that is the carbamate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 1-(2-chlorophenyl)ethyl hydrogen carbonate with the amino group of 3-({[4-(4-amino-3-methyl-1,2-oxazol-5-yl)phenyl]methyl}sulfanyl)propanoic acid.
A 3-[({4-[4-({[1-(2-chlorophenyl)ethoxy]carbonyl}amino)-3-methyl-1,2-oxazol-5-yl]phenyl}methyl)sulfanyl]propanoic acid that is the (S)-enantiomer of KI16425.
A 3-[({4-[4-({[1-(2-chlorophenyl)ethoxy]carbonyl}amino)-3-methyl-1,2-oxazol-5-yl]phenyl}methyl)sulfanyl]propanoic acid that is the (R)-enantiomer of KI16425.
A member of the class of pyrazoles carrying pyridin-2-yl and quinolin-4-yl substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively.
A guaiacyl lignin that is medioresinol in which one of the phenolic hydrogens is replaced by a guaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin that is scopoletin in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a guaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
An antagonist that binds to and deactivates TGFbeta receptors.
A guaiacyl lignin obtained by formal cyclocodensation between guaiacylglycerol and esculetin. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A pyranobenzodioxin obtained by formal cyclocodensation between syringylglycerol and esculetin. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin that is ferulic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a sulfoguaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A guaiacyl lignin that is ferulic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a sulfoguaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.
A purine 2',3'-dideoxyribonucleoside in which the nucleobase component is specified as adenine.
A guaiacyl lignin that is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

A dipeptide that is L-tryptophyl-L-leucinamide in which the N-terminal amino group has been converted to the corresponding (morpholin-4-yl)acetamide and in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen of the C-terminal amide has been replaced by a (1E)-5-methyl-1-(methylsulfonyl)hex-1-en-3-yl group. It is a selective proteasome inhibitor.
A guaiacyl lignin that is glycosmisic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a sulfo group.
A guaiacyl lignin that is glycosmisic acid in which the alcoholic hydrogen is replaced by a sulfo group.
A member of the class of pyrimidines carrying iodo and phenyl substituents at positions 4 and 6 respectively.
Any inhibitor of macrophage migration inhibitory factor (MIF).
A member of the class of oxadiazoloquinoxalines that is 1H-[1,2,4]oxadiazolo[4,3-a]quinoxaline substituted at position 1 by an oxo group.
An organic heterotricyclic compound that consists of an oxadiazole ring ortho-fused at any position to a quinoxaline ring system.
A TriHOME that is octadec-10-enoic acid in which the three hydroxy substituents are located at positions 9, 12 and 13.
A octadecanoid that is (10E,15Z)-octadecadienoic acid carrying three hydroxy substituents at positions 9, 12 and 13.
A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine obtained by formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of azelaic acid with the 1-hydroxy group of sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine.

A phenylindole that is 1H-indole which is substituted on the nitrogen by a p-chlorophenyl group, at position 5 by chlorine, and at position 3 by a piperidin-4-yl group, which is itself substituted on the nitrogen by a 2-(2-oxoimidazolidin-1-yl)ethyl group.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine obtained by formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of azelaic acid with the 1-hydroxy group of sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine.
A carotenoid ether that is spheroidene substituted at position 2 by a hydroxy group.
A member of the class of phenanthrolines that is 1,10-phenanthroline bearing two methyl substituents at positions 2 and 9.
A carotenoid ether that is spheroidene carrying two hydroxy groups, both at position 2.
An amidobenzoic acid obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of [(4-methylbenzene-1-sulfonyl)oxy]acetic acid with the amino group of 4-amino-2-hydroxybenzoic acid.
A sulfur-containing amino acid that is the sulfoxide obtained by formal oxygenation of the sulfur atom of pentahomomethionine.
